{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}} {{gaza blockade}}{{Expand list|date=October 2011}}
The '''"[[Freedom Flotilla II]]" participants''' had planned to sail on 5{{nbsp}}July 2011, but did not. Fewer than a few dozen people were believed to be planning to participate in the flotilla as of 7 July,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4088464,00.html|title=Fewer than 300 join flotilla|work=ynet}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jpost.com/Israel/Article.aspx?id=228372|title=Flotilla to Gaza founders as Greece stays the course|work=The Jerusalem Post – JPost.com}}</ref> though initial reports had suggested as many as 1,000 from 22 nations could be involved.{{Citation needed|date=July 2011}}
== Organizers ==
* [[Huwaida Arraf]], co-founder of [[International Solidarity Movement]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.turkishweekly.net/news/118497/flotilla-to-gaza-founders-as-greece-stays-the-course.html|title=Flotilla to Gaza founders as Greece stays the course|date=July 8, 2011|publisher=The Journal of Turkish Weekly}}</ref> * [[Medea Benjamin]], co-founder of [[Code Pink]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.cnn.com/2011-07-05/world/israel.greece.gaza.flotilla_1_greek-ships-greek-authorities-greek-ports/2?_s=PM:WORLD | work=CNN | title=Gaza-bound ship damaged after attempt to flee Greece | date=4 July 2011}}</ref> * [[Amin Abu Rashid]], Dutch Palestinian activist<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jpost.com/International/Article.aspx?id=227353|title=Hamas leader is brain behind Dutch flotilla|date=30 June 2011|publisher=[[The Jerusalem Post]]|website=www.jpost.com}}</ref> reported to be a member of the [[Al-Aqsa Foundation]] in Rotterdam.<ref>Olmer, Bart. [http://www.telegraaf.nl/binnenland/9643253/__Moslimclub_op_terreurlijst__.html "Moslimclub op terreurlijst"], De Telegraaf, 27 April 2011 (in Dutch)</ref> * [[Adam Shapiro (activist)|Adam Shapiro]], co-founder of International Solidarity Movement.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbn.com/cbnnews/insideisrael/2011/July/Flotilla-Organizers-Reject-Greek-Offer/|title=Flotilla Organizers Reject Greek Offer|date=4 July 2011|website=www.cbn.com|publisher=[[Christian Broadcasting Network]]}}</ref>
